name: Partido Liberal
description:
Liberal Party took first part in elections in 1949.
Over its existence, several factions formed and reformed (see Alexander 1982, 254–258):

+ 1885 — Independent Liberal Party [Doctrinario]
+ 1892 — Democratic Liberal Party (PLD)
+ 1920 — Aliancistas and Unionistas
+ 1930 — United Liberal Party (PLU) // during Ibanez regime
+ 1931 —  (new) Liberal Party (PL) // after Ibanez regime
+ 1933 —  (new) Liberal Party (PL) // during Alessandri regime
comment:
In 1930, attempts to unify Liberal factions failed.
In 1931, PLU, PLI-D, PLD still existed and new PL group formed.
In 1933, uniting Liberal factions succeeded.
